    "id": "davidwuw-54",
    "prompt": "A hyper-realistic isometric 3D render showing a miniature computer workspace inside a translucent mechanical keyboard keycap, specifically placed on the ESC key of a real matte-surface mechanical keyboard.\nInside the keycap, a tiny figure wearing a comfortable, textured hoodie sits in a modern ergonomic chair, focused on working at a glowing hyper-realistic computer screen. The space is filled with realistic miniature tech accessories: a real-material desk lamp, monitors with reflective effects, tiny speaker grilles, tangled cables, and ceramic mugs.\nThe base of the scene is composed of soil, rocks, and moss, with photographic-quality material textures and natural imperfections. The lighting inside the keycap simulates early morning natural sunlight, casting soft shadows and warm tones; while the exterior of the keycap is affected by cool-toned reflections from the surrounding keyboard environment.\nThe \"ESC\" lettering is etched on top of the translucent keycap with a subtle frosted glass effect — only faintly visible depending on the viewing angle.\nThe surrounding keys such as F1, Q, Shift, and CTRL are clearly visible with realistic material textures and lighting. The overall image appears as if captured by a high-end smartphone camera, with shallow depth of field, perfect white balance, and cinematic detail.",
